                                *******important to look upon*****

ans.append(String.valueOf(c).repeat(count)) // method 
List to string conversion




[(a, 3), (b, 2), (c, 1)]
Now, when we run the provided code:

First Iteration (Character 'a', Frequency 3):
c = 'a', count = 3
The inner loop runs 3 times, appending 'a' to the result each time.
After this, result = "aaa".

Second Iteration (Character 'b', Frequency 2):
c = 'b', count = 2
The inner loop runs 2 times, appending 'b' to the result each time.
After this, result = "aaabb".

Third Iteration (Character 'c', Frequency 1):
c = 'c', count = 1

The inner loop runs 1 time, appending 'c' to the result.
After this, result = "aaabbc".
Final result after the loop is: "aaabbc".
  
  
// Step : Build result string
       // string conversion
       StringBuilder ans = new StringBuilder();
       // here firstly it check first pair and print that much time then nested loop trminate and goes to next pair and so on
       for(Map.Entry<Character,Integer> entry : entries){ // it represent each pair like first (a,3) 
           char str = entry.getKey(); // represents a
           int cnt= entry.getValue(); // represents 3
           for(int i=0;i<cnt;i++){
                 ans= ans.append(str);
           }
       }
       return ans.toString(); 

    
          // in single loop
          StringBuilder ans = new StringBuilder();
          // here firstly it check first pair and print that much time then nested loop trminate and goes to next pair and so on
          for(Map.Entry<Character,Integer> entry : entries){ // it represent each pair like first (a,3) 
              char str = entry.getKey(); // represents a
              int cnt= entry.getValue(); // represents 3
              ans.append(String.valueOf(c).repeat(count));
          }
          return ans.toString(); 
   
    